             MIT's Approach to Graduate Student Union Negotiations

   MIT is bargaining in good faith with the GSU in order to reach an
   agreement on a first contract. This site shares the Institute's approach,
   key facts, resources and updates on the status of negotiations.

   [27]Read More

Upcoming Bargaining Sessions

   May 4

   [28]Guiding Principles
   [29]Key Issues
   [30]Negotiation Updates
   [31]Community Updates
   [32]Frequently Asked Questions

   The [33]MIT bargaining team is actively meeting and negotiating a first
   contract with MIT GSU, the union representing one third of the
   Institute***s graduate students. The students who are included in the
   GSU's bargaining unit are teaching assistants, research assistants, and
   instructor G's.

   This website is a central resource for [34]accurate and [35]timely
   information related to these negotiations, as well as the Institute***s
   valued relationship with our graduate students.

